The course deals with the history of the German-speaking countries from the Fall of Rome to the end of Cold War.  The course is divided into two equal periods: the first semester is devoted to the period up to the End of the Holy Roman Empire; the second semester; the second semester focuses on the period from the Napoleonic Wars until the German Reunification. The course consists of seminars; students will receive course materials.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide an overview of history of German-speaking countries during 2000 years, its main stages and key moments against the background of European history but also about different ways of treating history, creation of political myths and subjectivity of historical research.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has completed the course should know the main facts of  distinctive history of the German-speaking countries on the background of the history of Europe and be able to see it in the wider cultural context.
